## 5. System Architecture & Technical Design

### 5.1 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Why This Choice |
|---|---|---|
| Programming Language | Python 3.10+ | Beginner-friendly, vast ML ecosystem |
| ML Models | scikit-learn, XGBoost | Lightweight, no GPU required |
| Small LLM | Ollama + Phi-3 Mini | Local deployment, free, privacy-preserving |
| Simulation | SimPy | Standard for healthcare discrete-event simulation |
| Dashboard | Streamlit | Free, Python-native, no web dev skills needed |
| Database | SQLite | Zero-configuration, file-based, serverless |
| Data Processing | pandas, NumPy | Industry standard, well-documented |
| Visualization | Plotly, Matplotlib | Interactive charts, easy integration |
| Scheduling | APScheduler | Automated model retraining and data updates |

### 5.2 Hardware Requirements

**Minimum (Component A, B, D only):**
- CPU: Any modern processor (Intel i3 / AMD Ryzen 3 or better)
- RAM: 4 GB
- Storage: 10 GB free
- Cost: ~$300-500 for a refurbished desktop

**Recommended (All components including SLM):**
- CPU: Intel i5 / AMD Ryzen 5 or better
- RAM: 16 GB (for running small language models)
- Storage: 50 GB free
- Cost: ~$600-1000 for a standard desktop

**Contrast with enterprise AI systems:**
- Typical hospital AI: $50,000-500,000 initial + $10,000-50,000/year
- AWOS: $300-1,000 initial + $0/year (open-source software)

